Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them
onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.
> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%mins}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the @British Pork and Oregano Sausage Meat{225%g} into a large
#bowl{}. Mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking. IMPORTANT: Wash your
> hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, lay in the @British Streaky Bacon{4} rashers and fry
until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%mins} on each side. Transfer to a plate lined
with #kitchen paper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook
> bacon thoroughly.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat. Add the burgers and
fry until browned and cooked through, ~{5-6%mins} each side. Carefully turn
them every ~{2%mins} and lower the heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the burgers cook, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}.

Pop the @Onion Marmalade{40%g} into a small bowl and break it up with a
#spoon{}.

Cut the @Medium Tomato{1} into 2cm chunks.

When the burgers are cooked, remove the pan from the heat. Carefully place
the cheese on top of the burgers, followed by a spoonful of the onion
marmalade. Cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}), then set aside, off the heat, to
allow the cheese to melt, ~{3-4%mins}.

Meanwhile, halve the @Glazed Burger Buns{2}. Pop them onto a baking tray and
into oven to warm through, ~{2-3%mins}.

Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine the @Olive Oil for the Dressing{2%tbsp}
and @Red Wine Vinegar{12%ml}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a pinch of
@?sugar{}.

Mix well, then add the tomatoes and @Wild Rocket{40%g}. Toss to coat.

When everything's ready, pop the burgers and crispy bacon into the buns.
Serve on your plates with the wedges and salad alongside. Enjoy!